mainmatter.p:
The light-cone coordinates can be defined as two independent linear combinations of the time and a chosen spatial coordinate (conventionally x^1):
\begin {align*} x^+ \equiv \frac {1}{ \sqrt {2}} (X^0 + X^1) \\ x^- \equiv \frac {1}{ \sqrt {2}} (X^0 - X^1) \end {align*}
while other spatial coordinates remain unchanged. Thus the complete set of light-cone coordinates is (x^+,x^-,x^2,x^3).
